<div id="review_2662291593" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2662291593" />
    <a title="Barbara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/58819431-barbara"><img alt="Barbara" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2662291593?book_show_action=true">Jan 11, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Barbara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Barbara" href="/user/show/58819431-barbara">Barbara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2662291593" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer61319672344652666">A lovely gentle read about Edwardian country life, just before WW1. It takes a while to get to know so many characters, but well worth persisting. It&apos;s useful to have the Family Tress at the start of the book!<br/>There is quite a bit of descriptions of the countryside, but I think it helps you get a feel for the way of life.<br/>The Suffragette Movement is also dealt with and showed both sides - some of the countrywomen had no time for it!</span>
  <span id="freeText61319672344652666" style="display:none">A lovely gentle read about Edwardian country life, just before WW1. It takes a while to get to know so many characters, but well worth persisting. It's useful to have the Family Tress at the start of the book!<br />There is quite a bit of descriptions of the countryside, but I think it helps you get a feel for the way of life.<br />The Suffragette Movement is also dealt with and showed both sides - some of the countrywomen had no time for it!</span>
