<div id="review_3490679381" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3490679381" />
    <a title="Carolyn Agosta" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3882310-carolyn-agosta"><img alt="Carolyn Agosta" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1276691115p2/3882310.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3490679381?book_show_action=true">Aug 11, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carolyn Agosta" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carolyn Agosta" href="/user/show/3882310-carolyn-agosta">Carolyn Agosta</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3490679381" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1907456695336492793">Having read Delderfield&apos;s Swann Trilogy, I was interested in reading another. This one is set in the Edwardian period, before World War I, and while it does not have QUITE the sweep of the Swann Trilogy - at least not this first book of the three that make up the A Horseman Riding By trilogy, it still has a loving look at a bygone era, with strong and memorable characters who, together, create an image of rural England (whereas the Swann Trilogy is quite wrapped around industrial England). Delde</span>
  <span id="freeText1907456695336492793" style="display:none">Having read Delderfield's Swann Trilogy, I was interested in reading another. This one is set in the Edwardian period, before World War I, and while it does not have QUITE the sweep of the Swann Trilogy - at least not this first book of the three that make up the A Horseman Riding By trilogy, it still has a loving look at a bygone era, with strong and memorable characters who, together, create an image of rural England (whereas the Swann Trilogy is quite wrapped around industrial England). Delderfield maintains his high level of knowledge of how things were done and his skill in building that world for the readers, and allowing us to see how change creates all sorts of ripples. And sometimes not ripples, but tidal waves. I love how this book, along with the Swann Trilogy, shows that one man can set things in motion that affect many other people. An excellent read, and I look forward to the next two books in the set.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1907456695336492793" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


