<span id="freeTextContainer9735864078920584095">I &quot;inherited&quot; this from a family member and was skeptical about it, as it didn&apos;t look like the sort of thing I would usually enjoy, but to my surprise I loved it. It captures the essence of the countryside perfectly; the plot manages to maintain a good pace, but still holds tension well; there are some completely believable unbelievable happenings to provide dramatic flourish but it keeps a steady, jogging, calm rhythm, and relies on character and setting to keep you turning pages. A gentle yet </span>
  <span id="freeText9735864078920584095" style="display:none">I "inherited" this from a family member and was skeptical about it, as it didn't look like the sort of thing I would usually enjoy, but to my surprise I loved it. It captures the essence of the countryside perfectly; the plot manages to maintain a good pace, but still holds tension well; there are some completely believable unbelievable happenings to provide dramatic flourish but it keeps a steady, jogging, calm rhythm, and relies on character and setting to keep you turning pages. A gentle yet addictive read with brilliant descriptions of scenery and setting and some really wonderful characters.</span>
