<span id="freeTextContainer14824592150123941691">A very easy read that engaged me from the beginning. It is about a very different world in the early 20th century. Paul Craddock, despite being city born, comes back injured from the Boer war and decides he wants to try out farming. He is able to buy a big, run down estate in the West Country as his father had been a successful scrap metal merchant. Despite hating his fathers trade the money from it enable him to develop his small estate. It is about how he develops his new persona and grows in </span>
  <span id="freeText14824592150123941691" style="display:none">A very easy read that engaged me from the beginning. It is about a very different world in the early 20th century. Paul Craddock, despite being city born, comes back injured from the Boer war and decides he wants to try out farming. He is able to buy a big, run down estate in the West Country as his father had been a successful scrap metal merchant. Despite hating his fathers trade the money from it enable him to develop his small estate. It is about how he develops his new persona and grows in confidence and includes lots of interesting descriptions of the very different tenants on his estate.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14824592150123941691" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

